{
  "id": "spectrum",
  "name": "Adobe Spectrum",
  "website": "https://spectrum.adobe.com",
  "sources": [
    "https://unpkg.com/@adobe/spectrum-tokens@14.15.0/dist/json/variables.json",
    "https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/color-fundamentals/",
    "https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/color-system/"
  ],
  "description": "Adobe's design system, whose color themes are generated from target contrast ratios (the approach pioneered by Adobe's Leonardo tool). Every token ships independently designed light and dark values in @adobe/spectrum-tokens.",
  "philosophy": "Scales are not hand-picked swatches but contrast-generated: each step's lightness is converted into a target WCAG contrast ratio against the theme background, following a perceptually curved distribution (evaluated in the CIECAM02-UCS uniform color space, curved to counter Stevens' power law). As the index increases (blue-700 -> 900) contrast with the background increases, so colors get darker in light theme and lighter in dark theme; dark-theme targets are higher to stay perceptually consistent. Grays are fully desaturated to avoid chromatic adaptation and simultaneous-contrast illusions; every value is authored per scheme, not derived by inversion.",
